Regression Tests
----------------

    make test7    # set(ancestor_subsume) regression
    make test8    # list(resonators) regression

Both produce "THEOREM PROVED" and diagnostic counters.  Test7 also
shows Forward_subsumed/Back_subsumed totals (and Anc_subsume_blocked
when blocks occur).  Test8 confirms "N resonators installed" and a
successful proof in both decks.


Implementation Notes
--------------------

Feature A (resonators):

  ladr/unify.c:      match_resonator() -- new Wos-wildcard matcher
  ladr/unify.c:      is_any_var_sym() -- exposed any-var check
  ladr/weight.c:     init_resonators(), resonator_match_weight() --
                     new storage and lookup; weight() consults
                     resonators first, falls through to existing rules
  ladr/top_input.c:  accept_list("resonators", ...) -- registered in
                     provers.src/provers.c alongside existing lists

Feature B (ancestor subsumption):

  ladr/just.c:       proof_tree_weight() -- iterative tree-leaf
                     counter with memoization (O(|ancestors|))
  ladr/subsume.c:    anc_subsume(c, d, use_prf_weight) -- Otter's
                     variant tie-breaker
  provers.src/search.c:  flags ancestor_subsume and proof_weight
                         registered; hooks at forward-subsumption and
                         back-subsumption decision sites; new stat
                         anc_subsume_blocked is printed in "lots"/"all"
                         stats and serialized in checkpoints.


Compatibility
-------------

  - Input decks that do not use list(resonators) or set(ancestor_subsume)
    are behaviorally identical to the master branch.  All existing
    regression tests (test1..test6) pass unchanged.
  - Checkpoints from the master branch deserialize correctly: the new
    stat "anc_subsume_blocked" is treated as 0 when missing.
  - list(resonators) is serialized in new checkpoints alongside
    list(weights).


